article.headline: Mercer 84, Kennesaw State 77 (OT)
article.story: MACON, Ga. (AP) -- James Florence scored 23 points to help Mercer overcome a second-half deficit and defeat Kennesaw State 84-77 Saturday in overtime. Kennesaw State led by six points deep in the second half before Mercer rallied back to take a three point lead in the game's final seconds. With 24 seconds left, Kennesaw State's Ronell Wooten answered with a three point shot to tie the game, but the team only made 1 of 8 shots in overtime. Meanwhile, Mercer scored 4-of-5 shots to clinch victory. Mercer's Florence led all scorers with 23 points and Brendan Walker added 21 more. Andre Morgan led Kennesaw State with 22 points, including 4 three-point baskets. Wooten added 18 points -- all three-pointers -- while Shuan Stegall logged 15 points and 15 rebounds.
